Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of water to boil. Mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Finely chop @chili pepper{1}(finely chopped), removing seeds if you prefer less heat. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(sliced thin, greens and whites separated), keeping greens and whites separate. Trim and cut @green beans{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Halve @lime{1}(halved).

> We used ½ teaspoon kosher salt for this recipe.

Form the meatballs: In a #medium bowl{}, mix together @ground pork{8%ounce}, scallion whites, @Thai seasoning blend{1%teaspoon}, half the garlic, and a large pinch of @salt{1/2%teaspoon} and  @pepper{}. Form into 1-inch meatballs.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add meatballs and brown ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Add @water{1/4%cup} to pan, cover with a #large lid{}, and steam ~{2-3%minutes} (to cook meatballs through). Uncover and simmer on low until water evaporates. Remove meatballs from pan and set aside.

Cook the green beans: Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add green beans and toss until crisp-tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

> TIP: Add a few Tablespoons water to speed up the process.

Add half the pack of @yakisoba noodles{16%ounce} (save the other half for next time) to water, stir ~{2-3%minutes} until tender, yet chewy. Drain and rinse under cold water. Add chili and remaining @garlic{1%clove}(minced) to pan. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add noodles and stir until broken up completely.

Combine @soy sauce{1%ounce}, @honey{1%jar}, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup} in a #small bowl{}. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add meatballs, green beans, and soy mixture to pan. Toss until thoroughly combined and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Top with scallion greens and a squeeze of lime. Enjoy!